As of the 2020 census, there were 922 people, 488 housing units, and 455 families. There were 833 [[White Americans|White]] people, 1 [[African Americans|African American]], 13 [[Native Americans in the United States|Native Americans]], 2 [[Asian Americans|Asians]], 7 people from some other race, and 66 people from two or more races. There were 34 people from [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] origin.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Puget_Island_CDP,_Washington?g=160XX00US5356555 |access-date=2023-05-19 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry in Puget Island was 21.5% [[English Americans|English]], 8.7% [[German Americans|German]], 7.1% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], 4.9% [[Norwegian Americans|Norwegian]],1.8% [[Scottish Americans|Scottish]], 1.8% [[French Americans|French]], and 0.9% [[Italian Americans|Italian]].<ref name=":0" />

The median age was 60 years old. A total of 37.5% of the population were older than 65, with 22.5% being from 65 to 74 years, 12.7% being from 75 to 84 years, and 2.2% being 85 or older.<ref name=":0" />

The median household income was $56,929, with families having $58,401, and non-families having $56,087. A total of 10.6% of the population were in poverty, with 9.3% of people between the ages of 18 and 64 being in poverty, and 17.4% of people over 65 being in poverty.<ref name=":0" />

